questions.text: In general, would you say your health is:
Has anyone in your family ever been diagnosed by a doctor or prescribed medication for any of the following medical conditions?
What is your triglyceride level?
questions.textNote: Triglycerides are fats found in your blood and in fat tissue.

questions.text: What was your last high-density lipoprotein cholesterol reading?
Do you know your exact high-density lipoprotein cholesterol level?
What is your high-density lipoprotein level?
questions.textNote: Also known as “good” cholesterol, high-density lipoprotein cholesterol (HDL cholesterol) is an indicator of risk for heart attack or stroke.

questions.text: What was your last total cholesterol reading?
Do you know your exact total cholesterol level?
What is your total cholesterol level?
questions.textNote: Cholesterol is a waxy, fat-like substance. Your liver produces cholesterol in your body

questions.text: What was your last low-density lipoprotein cholesterol reading?
Do you know your exact low-density lipoprotein cholesterol level?
What is your low-density lipoprotein level?
questions.textNote: Also known as “bad” cholesterol, low-density lipoprotein cholesterol (LDL cholesterol) is an indicator of risk for heart attack or stroke.

questions.text: What is your random glucose level?
questions.textNote: This blood test measures the level of blood sugar taken at any time of the day without taking into account the individual’s intake of food.

questions.text: Do you know your exact HbA1c level?
What is your HbA1C reading?
questions.textNote: The HbA1c test is a blood test that provides information about a person’s average levels of blood glucose, also called blood sugar, over the past 3 months.

questions.text: Have you ever been diagnosed by a doctor or prescribed medication for any of the following medical conditions? (Select all the conditions that apply)
Allergies
questions.textNote: An allergy is an abnormal immune reaction against a typically harmless substance, called an allergen.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for allergies?
Are you currently under medical care for allergies?
Arthritis
questions.textNote: Arthritis is inflammation of one or more of the joints.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for arthritis?
Are you currently under medical care for arthritis?
Asthma
questions.textNote: Asthma is a chronic condition that affects a person's respiratory or breathing system.

questions.text: Heart Burn or Acid Flux
questions.textNote: Gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD) is a common condition where acid from the stomach leaks up into the oesophagus (gullet).

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for heart burn or acid reflux?
Are you currently under medical care for heart burn or acid reflux?
Heart Disease
questions.textNote: Heart disease describes a range of conditions that affect the heart

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for heart diseases?
Are you currently under medical care for heart diseases?
Blood Pressure
questions.textNote: High blood pressure, or hypertension, occurs when the force of blood pushing against the walls of the arteries as the heart pumps blood is too high.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for high blood pressure?
Are you currently under medical care for high blood pressure?
Cholesterol
questions.textNote: Cholesterol is a waxy, fat-like substance, produced by the liver.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for high cholesterol?
Are you currently under medical care for high cholesterol?
Menopause
questions.textNote: Menopause is a natural part of ageing caused by the decline of a woman's oestrogen levels that usually occurs between 45 and 55 years of age, with 51 being the average age.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for menopause?
Are you currently under medical care for menopause?
Migraine Headache
questions.textNote: A migraine is a severe headache that causes extreme throbbing pain or a pulsing sensation usually on just one side of the head.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for migraine headaches?
Are you currently under medical care for migraine headaches?
Osteoporosis
questions.textNote: Osteoporosis occurs when bones become brittle and fragile from loss of tissue, typically as a result of hormonal changes, or deficiency of ca lcium or vitamin D.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for osteoporosis?
Are you currently under medical care for osteoporosis?
Sleep Disorder
questions.textNote: Sleep disorders are changes in sleeping patterns.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for sleep disorder?
Are you currently under medical care for sleep disorder?
Stroke
questions.textNote: A stroke is a serious, life-threatening medical condition that occurs when the blood supply to part of the brain is interrupted or severely reduced, and the b rain tissue is deprived of oxygen and nutrients.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for a stroke?
Are you currently under medical care for a stroke?
Thyroid Disease
questions.textNote: Thyroid disease is a common problem that can cause symptoms because of over- or under-functioning of the thyroid gland.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for thyroid disease?
Are you currently under medical care for thyroid disease?
Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for asthma?
Are you currently under medical care for asthma?
Backpain
questions.textNote: Back pain can range from a dull, constant ache to a sudden, sharp pain that originates from structures in the spine.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for back pain?
Are you currently under medical care for back pain?
Cancer
questions.textNote: Cancer refers to any one of a large number of diseases characterised by the development of abnormal cells that divide uncontrollably and have the ability to invade and destroy normal body tissue.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for cancer?
Are you currently under medical care for cancer?
Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD)
questions.textNote: Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) is a chronic (long-term) inflammatory lung disease that causes obstructed airflow from the lungs.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD)?
Are you currently under medical care for Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD)?
Chronic pain
questions.textNote: Chronic pain is often defined as any pain lasting  more than 12 weeks.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for chronic pain?
Are you currently under medical care for chronic pain?
Depression
questions.textNote: Depression is a mood disorder that affects people in various ways and can cause a wide variety of symptoms - ranging from on-going feelings of unhappiness and hopelessness, to losing interest in activities and feeling very tearful.

questions.text: Has your physician recommended regular prescription drug use for depression?
Are you currently under medical care for depression?
Diabetes
questions.textNote: Diabetes is a disease that affects the body's ability to produce or use insulin.
